Have developed such a love hate relationship with digital visibility. Ironically, when I’m the most present I’m the least concerned with portraying a picture perfect life. 

Grateful for the way life has been slowing me down while overwhelming me with such an embarrassment of beautiful moments. Shifting my focus to experiencing genuine happiness rather than the appearance of happiness is my act of rebellion in such a superficial world.

Goodbye being young, as my little brother would say. 

Definitely was looking around thinking “oh wow it’s somebody else’s birthday too! “ 

Grateful to have such an an amazing life: amazing friends, a loving family, freedom to show up as myself everywhere I go, an amazing  career, love, purpose, my health and ,above all, true equanimity in every sense of the word. 

Appreciate the love y’all.
